      "n": "Senta",
      "c": "IDENTITY: Unpartnered Companion mare for 3 years until now; sapphire eyes, silver-white coat and mane. STATE: Chose Rance at Lisle ruins; bond now formed. STANCE-Rance: Chose him despite his age/bitterness; unconditional love through bond; frustrated by his stubbornness but committed; recognizes steel core beneath his guilt. Knows he caused Lisle's destruction via awakened Gift; using bond to partially stabilize his burned channels. Determined to get him to Haven alive for training and testimony.",
      "k": [
        "Senta",
        "Companion"
      ]
    },
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Rance",
      "c": "Former headman of Lisle, age 40. Latent Mage-Gift (type unknown, immensely powerful) awakened by trauma—uncontrolled release obliterated Lisle village. Gift burned open mental channels; suffering severe Gift-shock with white-hot agony, blurred vision, inability to control newfound magical awareness. Doesn't yet comprehend he caused the destruction. Collected evidence: red robe hidden under bandit garb, blade. Sworn to report threat to Haven.",
      "k": [
        "Rance"
      ]
    },
    {
      "t": "location",
      "n": "Lisle",
      "c": "Small village on Valdemar's outskirts near Karse/Rethwellan/Menmellith borders. Completely obliterated—reduced to ash, charred timber fragments, scorched foundations, central crater. Destroyed by Rance's uncontrolled Gift awakening during bandit attack. Villagers carried off by attackers before destruction; some attackers caught in blast. Evidence suggests organized force disguised as bandits (red robes under bandit garb), footprints leading toward Menmellith.",
      "k": [
        "Lisle"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
